data.name: label1.Text
data.value:
This program allows users of both the Steam and Uplay Versions of Rainbow Six Siege to seamlessly switch between both accounts without having to install the game twice. This gives players the ability to save 80-130GB of storage that is occupied by a second installation.
To start installation to make account switching a two-click process, click next.

data.name: label4.Text
data.value:
After uninstalling the Uplay Version, you will see a little "Locate installed game" option under download. Click on that and navigate to your Steam Version's Installation.

This may be different for you.

data.name: label6.Text
data.value:
If you did the last step correctly, you should see that Uplay will start verifying files. Wait until this process is done and let it download the few files that it needs to run. (This may take a while depending on your hard drive or SSD speeds)
In the meantime, you can continue to the next step.

data.name: label2.Text
data.value:
This allows the application to know where to copy the correct files to the correct place on your computer. If this is wrong, then you'll be stuck with the Uplay Version.
Make sure you use the same location that you used for locating the game in Uplay.
